In `queryViaMulticast`, the catch block only catches `IOException`. However, `buildQuery` can throw an `IllegalArgumentException` (via `require(bytes.size in 1..63)`) if any label in the hostname exceeds 63 bytes. Since `IllegalArgumentException` is a `RuntimeException`, it will bypass this catch block and crash the application.

Consider catching `Exception` instead of `IOException` to safely handle any unexpected runtime exceptions during the query construction or packet parsing.

```suggestion
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            Timber.w(e, "mDNS query for %s failed", hostname)
        }
```

